Question:
You are given a string array events.
Initially,
score = 0
and counter = 0. Each element in events is one of the following:
"0"
, "1"
) "2", "3",
"4"
"6": Add that value to the total score.
• "W": Increase the counter by 1. No score is added.
• "WD": Add 1 to the total score.
• "NB": Add 1 to the total score.
Process the array from left to right. Stop processing when either:
• All elements in events
have been processed, or
• The counter becomes 10.
Return an integer array [score, counter], where:
• score is the final total score.
counter is the final counter value.
Example 1:
Input: events = ["1", "4", "W", "6", "WD"]
Output: [12, 1]

Solution:
class Solution {
    public int[] scoreValidator(String[] events) {
        int sc=0,w=0;
        for(String s:events){
            if(w==10) break;
            else if(s.equals("W")) w++;
            else if(s.equals("WD") || s.equals("NB")) sc++;
            else sc+= Integer.parseInt(s);
        }
        int[] ans = new int[2];
        ans[0] = sc;
        ans[1] = w;
        return ans;
    }
}
